config VAMS_PCI
	tristate "Virtual Accelerator Management Subsystem PCIe support"
	depends on PCI && PCI_MSI
	help
	  Build the thin host discovery and interrupt driver for the VAMS QEMU
	  PCIe endpoint. Queue and command transport support is added separately
	  when the endpoint advertises the DMA capability. The driver validates
	  BAR0 identity and ABI versions, negotiates a DMA mask, and installs the
	  two required MSI-X interrupt handlers.

config VAMS_PCI_TESTING
	bool "VAMS PCI probe fault-injection controls"
	depends on VAMS_PCI
	help
	  Add module parameters that inject failures after each probe resource
	  acquisition and exercise both MSI-X paths. This is intended only for
	  disposable test guests. Production builds omit the parameters and their
	  interrupt-forcing behavior. Enable this only in an isolated QEMU guest
	  used by the integration test.
